   "source": [
    "# Gaussian Process (with Squidward)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# GP Package\n",
    "from squidward import gpr\n",
    "from squidward.kernels import distance, kernel_base\n",
    "\n",
    "# For generating and visualizing data\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import model_viz as mv\n",
    "import generate_data as gd"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_train, x_test, \\\n",
    "y_train, y_test, \\\n",
    "x_true, y_true = gd.get_data(N=500, \n",
    "                             limits=(-10, 10), \n",
    "                             missing_data=False, \n",
    "                             heteroscedastic=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mv.demo_plot(x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test, x_true, y_true)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "d = distance.RBF(2.0, 5.0**2)\n",
    "kernel = kernel_base.Kernel(d, 'k1')\n",
    "model = gpr.GaussianProcessInversion(kernel=kernel, var_l=10**2, inv_method='solve')\n",
    "model.fit(x_train,y_train)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# generate data to plot posterior of model\n",
    "x = np.linspace(-10, 10, 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "# pull the parameters of the posterior distribution\n",
    "mean, var = model.posterior_predict(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot posterior of model\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
    "plt.title(\"GP Posterior Distribution\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(x_train,y_train,label='Train Data', c='c', alpha=0.2)\n",
    "plt.scatter(x_test,y_test,label='Test Data', c='r', alpha=0.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(x, mean)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,

   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  }
